Beneath these headline moves, the neutral machinery of government was being hollowed out and repurposed. The Department of Government Efficiency, run by Elon Musk, continued its ideological purge of agencies under the guise of cost savings, even as its own program was projected to cost more than it saved. DOGE operatives with little experience were embedded in departments like HUD, where a college student used AI tools to scan and propose rewrites of regulations. At the National Park Service, a planned \'93reduction in force\'94 threatened to cut thousands of positions, adding to earlier losses. The Peace Corps offered buyouts to staff as part of a DOGE-driven restructuring. And in April, Trump signed an order reclassifying tens of thousands of civil service roles as political appointments, reviving and expanding the old \'93Schedule F\'94 concept. Together, these steps turned a professional bureaucracy into a patronage system and opened core state functions to private contractors and corporate partners. Neutral capacity gave way to loyal capacity.\
